<P>
   CAMBODIA-WARCRIMES (Phum Thmei, Cambodia) _ As Cambodia and the
outside world prepare for the possibility of trials for perhaps a
dozen Khmer Rouge leaders, a large unanswered _ and generally
unasked _ question is how to deal with the people who actually took
part in the torture and the killing, or even how to think of them.
``Why should only the the top leaders take responsibility?'' said
Youk Chhang, director of the Documentation Center of Cambodia, a
private agency that is collecting evidence of Khmer Rouge crimes.
By Seth Mydans.
</P>
