<P>
   NISSAN-MARKETPLACE (Tokyo) _ For sale: A piece of the world's
sixth-largest car company. Some $20 billion in debt, but a
fixer-upper with promise. Interested parties may apply to Yoshikazu
Hanawa, president of Nissan Motor Co. Hanawa has embarked on a
sales campaign never before seen in Japan and perhaps in the world.
Nearly every day for more than a week, he has been hawking his
company. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   ANHEUSERBUSCH-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Like a tavern owner who
feels expansive enough to buy the house a round of drinks,
Anheuser-Busch Inc. is spending a record sum on the most commercial
time it has ever bought during a Super Bowl. By Stuart Elliott.
