<HEADER>
A2180 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-BARKLEY-JORDAN-HN     01-21 0534
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BARKLEY-JORDAN-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By EDDIE SEFKO  
 c. 1998, Houston Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LA QUINTA, Calif. _ Michael Jordan has endorsed the Rockets'
acquisition of Scottie Pippen as a move that will bring more
championship banners to Houston, especially since Charles Barkley
now is set to go along for the ride.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley insisted Wednesday at the Bob Hope Chrysler Classic that
he would hold off on making a decision about which team he will
play for in the upcoming NBA season. However, several sources late
Wednesday said Barkley was preparing to sign a one-year contract
with the Rockets today, which would free the team to proceed with
other roster moves, including the acquisition of Pippen from
Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockets must get far enough under the salary cap to
accommodate Pippen's new salary, which will start at nearly $11
million. With Barkley signing for $1 million for this abbreviated
season, it will reduce his salary-cap slot by more than $3 million.
</P>
<P>
   The signing of Barkley will allow the Rockets to consummate the
trade for Pippen, sending a draft pick and Roy Rogers to the Bulls.
That means the Rockets' new Big Three of Pippen, Barkley and Hakeem
Olajuwon will be in place for the start of training camp today,
although Barkley likely will remain in Southern California for the
next three days to continue playing in the pro-am portion of the
golf tournament.
</P>
<P>
   The Barkley-Olajuwon-Pippen triangle would make the Rockets the
preseason favorite for this year's NBA championship, Jordan said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was just telling these guys how there's going to be three
more titles with Pippen in Houston,'' Jordan said in Barkley's
direction as the pair visited with galleryites and media members
during a lull in the tournament Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   To that, Barkley shot back: ``I don't have three years left in
this body. I don't even know if I have three months left.''
</P>
<P>
   It is uncertain how serious the threat was that Barkley might
have ended up somewhere other than Houston. The most likely
explanation is that his delay on Wednesday in announcing he was
ready to re-sign with the Rockets was simply because he did not
want to be taken away from the golf outing, which he, Jordan and
good friend Roy Green, the former NFL receiver, had been planning
for some time.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley said the lure of playing with Pippen and Olajuwon in the
same lineup is great. But he said there were other appealing
options as well.
</P>
<P>
   ``Getting Scottie was a great pickup for the Rockets,'' Barkley
said. ``He's one of the greatest two or three players in the
league.''
</P>
<P>
   And there is more good news for the Rockets: Barkley is ready to
play basketball.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley is about as close to buff as he can get with his stocky
frame. After ballooning to about 280 pounds, according to his
friends, soon after last season ended, Barkley has slimmed down and
is within a few Miller Lites of his playing weight, which is
advertised at 252 pounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm in great shape,'' Barkley said. ``I've been working out
just to see if I could get myself in great shape and I feel really
good. I'm looking forward to playing this season.''
</P>
<P>
   So are the Rockets.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
