<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic storfy has have been reinstated
for use by clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, Jan.
21. If you have any questions, please contact the Republic News
Desk at (602) 271-8108.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; (For immediate release) &QL; 
QUAYLE _ After launching an attack on ``liberal Republicans,'' Dan
Quayle is taking his first formal step toward running in 2000.
Quayle will file exploratory campaign papers today in Washingon,
and then make a public declaration on ``Larry King Live,'' the same
TV show that Ross Perot used to launch his presidential campaign.
Quayle discusses this and other things _ like his thinly-veiled jab
at George Bush _ in an interview with ``The Arizona Republic.'' By
MICHAEL MURPHY. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
