<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cross-license teams up big-name wrestlers, WB cartoon characters
 &HT;    By Jim Bohman
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ If a colorful T-shirt with wrestling's Bill
Goldberg snarling at Yosemite Sam is something you gotta have, hang
on, it's coming.
</P>
<P>
   Littlefield, Adams &AMP; Co., a Huber Heights T-shirt imprinter that
supplies Wal-Mart, Kmart and Target, has signed cross licensing
agreements that will make such eye-catching shirts possible.
</P>
<P>
   The agreements with World Championship Wrestling, a long-time
client, and Warner Brothers' Looney Tunes are a first for
Littlefield, Adams, which produces decorative apparel.
</P>
<P>
   World Championship Wresting T-shirts were a major contributor to
Littlefield, Adams' $25 million in 1998 sales, according to Warren
Rawls, chief financial officer.
</P>
<P>
   The agreements cover men's and boy's T-shirts, sweatshirts,
shooter shirts and long sleeve shirts, said Michael Balber, chief
executive officer.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are thrilled to be back with Warner Brothers and believe
this cross-license will allow us to create humorous, more light
hearted portrayals of wrestling using Taz (the Tasmanian Devil),
Bugs Bunny and other Looney Tunes characters which are instantly
recognizable by the consumer,'' Balber said. ``Combining these two
famous properties produces merchandise which appeals to consumers
in a very broad age range.''
</P>
<P>
   Balber said the new T-shirts will be in mass merchandise stores
around the end of February.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
