 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE FEATURES BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These feature stories are moving today to clients of the New
York Times News Service. Stories are for release Friday, January
22, 1999, unless otherwise embargoed.
</P>
<P>
   So specialty editors won't have to look at every day's budget,
Cox's features budgets have daily themes according tothis schedule:
</P>
<P>
   Monday for Tuesday: Technology
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday for Wednesday: Automotive
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday for Thursday: Food, CD reviews, video reviews
</P>
<P>
   TODAY: Movie reviews, travel, books and fashion
</P>
<P>
   Friday for Saturday: Religion, science &AMP; health, and home &AMP;
garden
</P>
<P>
   In addition, separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports,
business and commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. An ETA is given if a
story will move after 8 p.m. Eastern.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SAVE TIME: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are available for
purchase in paginated form: www.nytsyn.com/pageexpress.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL _ TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   COXNET-TRAVEL 0119: Tired of playing with that talking Furby
already? Check out another fur ball's first big venture into
high-tech entertainment: DisneyQuest, a five-story,
100,000-square-foot mall of interactive games. (Lomartire, Palm
Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   DESTINATIONS _ SOUTH BEACH _ At the Clay Hotel, in the middle of
the night, among a small labyrinth of courtyards, it's not hard to
close your eyes and hear the spin of a roulette wheel. Is that Al
Capone striding toward you in a narrow hall, his fedora cocked to
one side? That wisp of tobacco smoke you smelled _ is it just a
late-returning guest or ``Scarface'' returning to one of his old
haunts? The Clay, you see, was home to the mobsters' 1920s-30s
gambling syndicate. (Park, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet Travel page for the current week. This
layout is now available.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SANDESTIN _ DESTIN, Fla. _ In the winter, things are
definitely low key at the 2,400-acre Resort at Sandestin, halfway
between Panama City and Pensacola. Even the snowbirds had only
begun to trickle down from the great frozen North. While there was
plenty to keep us occupied _ golfing, shopping, salon pampering,
dining, exploring Jolee Island nature preserve _ at times, it
seemed as if we had the place all to ourselves. But all this may be
about to change. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This package is embargoed until Sunday, Jan. 24.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-DESTIN-SIDE _ DESTIN, Fla. _ We venture beyond the
manicured confines of Sandestin, in search of Old Destin, now
mostly hidden by high-rises, strip malls, mega Walmarts and
roadside amusement centers (bungee-jumping, race car driving and
gooney golf, anyone?). Truth is: Destin in pretty much in
hibernation in the dead of winter. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-DESTIN-IFYOUGO _ DESTIN, Fla. _ Details on
accommodations, dining and places to shop and play. (Thrasher,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NOTES _ Going Places (travel notes) column. (Thrasher,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed until Sunday, Jan. 24.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-FESTIVALS _ Southern happenings. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVEDTRAVEL-IDITAROD _ ANCHORAGE, Alaska _ I
knew the Iditarod Trail Sled Dog Race was an expedition in
extremes. I knew it was a race that attracts odd personalities as
it snakes across Alaska's rugged terrain. Then I saw the Poodle
Man. This and other adventures surrounding the Iditarod. (Houck,
Palm Beach Post). WITH PHOTOS. MOVED WITH
</P>
<P>
   NORTHERN LIGHTS _ MCGRATH, Alaska _ The showering splendor of
light called aurora borealis. An explanation and commentary on its
beauty. (Houck, Palm Beach Post) MOVED
</P>
