<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-21 12:30 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2628 &Cx1f; tad-z
r w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CONGRESS-BUSINESS-LIS     01-21 0475
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CONGRESS-BUSINESS-LIST-$ADV24- </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TOP PRIORITIES OF BIGGEST BUSINESS LOBBIES FOR 1999
 &HT;    With CONGRESS-BUSINESS. Moving in (w) Washington and (f)
financial categories for release Sunday, Jan. 24.
 &HT;    Eds: Logos and mugs of top officers for the groups listed below
have been placed in the COX-CONGRESS-BUSINESS folder in the
Business folder on the Cox server. For trim purposes, items below
for each organization are listed in order of priority.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   NATIONAL FEDERATION OF INDEPENDENT BUSINESS
</P>
<P>
   _ Cut taxes for individuals and businesses and scrap the federal
tax code.
</P>
<P>
   _ To save Social Security without higher payroll taxes, divert
part of taxes to individual investment accounts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Oppose health care mandates, exempt small-business health
insurance plans from state regulations, increase tax breaks for
people who buy their own health insurance.
</P>
<P>
   _ Reduce regulations and lawsuit burdens on businesses.
</P>
<P>
   _ Block increases in minimum wage.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. CHAMBER OF COMMERCE
</P>
<P>
   _ Protect businesses from lawsuits.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cut taxes for individuals and businesses.
</P>
<P>
   _ Save Social Security without higher payroll taxes by diverting
part of the taxes to individual investment accounts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Approve normal trade relations with China and fast-track
procedures for trade treaties.
</P>
<P>
   _ Exempt small-business health insurance pools from state
regulations, and block stiffer federal regulations for health
plans.
</P>
<P>
   _ Support ``improved'' schools and worker training, ``sensible''
immigration and ``more flexible'' workplaces.
</P>
<P>
   _ Oppose union efforts to raise the minimum wage, tighten safety
and health rules for workplaces or pass anti-blacklisting laws.
</P>
<P>
   _ Block ``unproven'' environmental regulations.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF MANUFACTURERS
</P>
<P>
   _ Cut taxes for individuals and businesses.
</P>
<P>
   _ Support normal trade relations with China, fast-track
procedures for trade treaties and International Monetary Fund
support, and oppose export controls and trade sanctions.
</P>
<P>
   _ Protect health plans from lawsuits and federal mandates.
</P>
<P>
   _ Save Social Security by diverting ``a substantial portion'' of
current payroll taxes to individual investment accounts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Help technology by changes in laws on tax credits, patents,
export controls, product codes, intellectual property and limits on
corporate liability for Year 2000 bugs in products or services.
</P>
<P>
   _ Turn federal training programs into block grants, encourage
choice and competition among schools, and expand tax incentives for
education.
</P>
<P>
   _ Offer businesses lawsuit protection, ``prudent'' electricity
deregulation and incentives _ rather than mandates _ to protect the
environment, safety and health.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
