<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Opening this weekend ``Gloria''
 &HT;    By Kathy Janich
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  The movie: ``Gloria,'' a drama/thriller about a woman, a boy
and a chase.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The plot: A woman's life is turned upside down when she's
forced to protect a 6-year-old boy running from the mob.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The cast: Sharon Stone, George C. Scott, Bonnie Bedelia and
Cathy Moriarty. Jean-Luke Figueroa plays Nicky, the little boy.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Directed by: Sidney Lumet, whose credits include ``Serpico''
(1973), ``Dog Day Afternoon'' (1975), ``Network'' (1976), ``Equus''
(1977), ``The Wiz'' (1978) and ``The Verdict'' (1982).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Rated: R for language and violence.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The buzz: Not prescreened for critics, a really bad sign
considering the talent _ Stone, Lumet _ attached to the project.
</P>
<P>
   _ Kathy Janich writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
