<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    You be the critic
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   `Shakespeare in Love'
</P>
<P>
   There are two great tragedies involved with ``Shakespeare in
Love.'' The first is Shakespeare's masterpiece ``Romeo and
Juliet.'' The second is that this film is only at five metro
(Atlanta) theaters. Excellent writing and flawless performances all
around (even from Ben Affleck, who redeems himself after the
jaw-droppingly awful ``Armageddon''). Don't wait and rent this
film; it's truly worth your seven bucks.
</P>
<P>
   Porter Watkins, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   `Star Trek: Insurrection'
</P>
<P>
   Futuristic techno-babble aside, there's much fun to be had in
this third film outing with the ``Next Generation'' gang. Director
Jonathan Frakes keeps things blasting along at a lively pace, while
F. Murray Abraham makes a formidable villain; Picard and company
(surprise!) save the day while lightening up and even making time
for the ladies.
</P>
<P>
   Stephen Hall, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   `A Civil Action'
</P>
<P>
   This movie characterizes John Travolta as an oxymoron: He's a
``principled lawyer.'' He loses everything in a case he could have
settled, because he let his pride get in the way of his judgment.
Robert Duvall is excellent as the company lawyer who teaches
Travolta that the truth has nothing to do with a court of law.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Schwartz, Chamblee (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   `The Faculty'
</P>
<P>
   I am definitely not one for ``teen-slasher flicks.'' Well, ``The
Faculty'' does have teenagers, but the only slashing is from
aliens. I doubted the director Robert Rodriguez at first in his
choice for this movie, but after seeing it I was pleasantly
surprised. It has humor, good special effects and great editing.
This one will only intrigue you, not bore you.
</P>
<P>
   Saxon Brack, Columbus (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   We're looking for movie fans who want to add their opinions to
our film coverage. To qualify, send us a brief review, preferably
of no more than 50 words, about a recent movie. Send your review,
name, address and telephone number to:
</P>
<P>
   Reader Movie Response
