<P>
   SUNDAY - JAN. 24
</P>
<P>
   POPEADVANCE _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Pope John Paul II comes to the
Midwest as the American Catholic Church and its 61 million members
struggle harder than ever to evangelize Generation Y and to hold on
to young people who have grown up in the church but drifted. Priest
shortages are rampant and the number choosing religious life
dwindles. Crowds of youth will come to see the pope, but dismiss
his moral mandates. As the aged pope nears the end of his papacy,
the future of the church lies in their hands. Will they accept
church law which John Paul has declared ``immutable'' on issues
such as celibacy of priests, birth control, abortion,
homosexuality, and women in the pulpit? A contrasting of their
views with older Catholics. What are the expectations of young
people from Dayton who will pilgrimage to St. Louis? (Lyles, Dayton
Daily News) 30 inches. MOVING FRIDAY, JAN. 22 FOR SUNDAY, JAN. 24
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY _ JAN. 26
</P>
<P>
   POPE26 _ ST. LOUIS _ St. Louis prepares for papal visit. (Lyles,
Dayton Daily News)
