<HEADER>
A2818 &Cx1f; tad-z
u t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRAVEL-DESTIN-IFYOUGO     01-21 0868
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-DESTIN-IFYOUGO24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    EMBARGOED UNTIL JANUARY 24
 &HT;    If you go: Destin, Florida
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  GETTING THERE
</P>
<P>
   (From Atlanta) Take I-85 south to I-185, then take Phenix City
exit and travel U.S. 80 west to U.S. 431. Go south on U.S. 431,
picking up U.S. 231 in Dothan, Ala. Continue south to I-10, then
west to Exit 14 (U.S. 331), then south to U.S. 98. Turn right and
drive about seven miles; the Market Shops at the Resort at
Sandestin will be on your left. It's about 330 miles from Atlanta,
about a six-hour drive. AirTran flies to Fort Walton Beach for $39
one way.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  STAYING AT SANDESTIN
</P>
<P>
   Sandestin offers 700 units including beach high-rises, villas
and an inn on the bay. Rates vary by size and season. For example,
Beachside Tower units from suites to three-bedrooms are $100-$210
through March 10; $185-$375, March 11-31, April 11-May 26 and Aug.
29-Sept. 2; $240-$575, April 1-10, May 27-Aug. 28 and Sept. 3-4.
</P>
<P>
   The least expensive accommodations are at the inn, where rates
are $70-$100 through March 10; $130-$170, March 11-31, April 11-May
26 and Aug. 29-Sept. 2; and $155-$200, April 1-10, May 27-Aug. 28
and Sept. 3-4. Weekly rates also available. Call 1-800-277-0800 for
reservations or check the Web site at http://www.sandestin.com.
</P>
<P>
   The Sandestin Hilton, while on the same property, is
independently managed by Hilton International. Rates through March
18 are $120-$190 per night. Reservations: 1-800-
</P>
<P>
   367-1271.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  THE B&AMP;B ALTERNATIVE
</P>
<P>
   The Henderson Park Inn is an upscale bed-and-breakfast on the
beach at the end of a quiet road on the eastern boundary of
Henderson State Park. The Old New England-style inn with cedar
shake siding and a green mansard roof was built in 1992 and
features fine dining at the Verandah. Rates through Feb. 28 are
$114-$188 per night for one to two nights, $94-$163 for three to
six nights, $460-$812 for a week. 2700 Scenic Highway 98 East,
Destin. 1-800-336-4853.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  OTHER LODGINGS
</P>
<P>
   For information on Destin, Fort Walton Beach and Okaloosa Island
_ the Okaloosa County communities west of Sandestin _ call the
Emerald Coast Convention and Visitors Bureau at 1-800-322-3319 or
check the Web at http://www.destin-fwb.com.
</P>
<P>
   For information on lodging throughout the Beaches of South
Walton _ which stretch from Sandestin east to Panama City Beach and
include 19 coastal communities (among them Grayton Beach, Seaside
and Seagrove Beach) _ call the South Walton Tourism Development
Council at 1-800-822-6877 or check the Web site at http://www
</P>
<P>
   .beachesofsouthwalton.com.
</P>
<P>
   These tourism agencies can provide information on the hundreds
of restaurants along the coast in Okaloosa and Walton counties.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  UPCOMING EVENTS
</P>
<P>
   ``Picnics in Paradise'' Spring Concert Series at the Resort at
Sandestin, featuring kids' events, gourmet picnic foods and
beverages, Thursdays from March 18 to April 29. 850-267-8092.
</P>
<P>
   Seaside's Ruskin Place Artist Colony's ``Big'' Arts Spring
Festival is March 18-21. 850-864-7800.
</P>
<P>
   The first Barbecue Rhythm &AMP; Blues Festival is March 19-20 under
the moss-draped oaks at Eden State Gardens in historic Point
Washington. Food. 850-231-4544.
</P>
<P>
   The Appellation Trail: The 13th Annual Sandestin Wine Festival
is April 15-18 (850-267-8092), followed by Seaside's Spring Wine
Festival April 30-May 2 (850-231-5424).
</P>
<P>
   A juried fine arts festival May 8-9 at Eden State Gardens winds
up the 10-day ArtsQuest '99 at locations throughout South Walton.
850-231-0885.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ATTRACTIONS/RECREATION
</P>
<P>
   Morgan's Family Entertainment Center with 160 futuristic arcade
games, virtual sports, golf simulator, soft-play maze, motion
simulation rides and billiards. At Silver Sands Factory Stores,
850-654-3320.
</P>
<P>
   The Track Recreation Center with go-carts, bumper boats, bumper
cars and mini-golf, 1125 U.S. 98 East, Destin. 850-654-
</P>
<P>
   4668.
</P>
<P>
   Big Kahuna's, home of ``the world's largest tropical golf'' with
a 54-hole mini-course with jungle theme. Also Little Kahuna's
Kiddieland, go-carts and Grand Prix track. 1007 U.S. 98 East,
Destin. 850-837-4061.
</P>
<P>
   Rollin Wheels skating rink, 122 Poinciana Blvd. (across from
Silver Sands), Destin. 850-650-0661.
</P>
<P>
   Paradise Yacht Charters offers sailboat cruises on the Spanish
Moon, from Baytowne Marina at the Resort at Sandestin. 850-651-3569
or 850-267-7777.
</P>
<P>
   Glass-Bottom Boat Dolphin Cruises and Boogies Water Sports, at
the foot of Destin Bridge on U.S. 98 next to Fat Tuesday.
850-654-7787.
</P>
<P>
   Deep-sea fishing on the Florida Girl from Capt. Dave's
Restaurant and Marina, one-half mile east of the Destin Bridge
(850-837-6422). Also, Capt. Dave's Charter Service (850-654-7878)
and pontoon and Jet Ski rentals at Capt. Dave's Marina
(850-837-6357.)
</P>
<P>
   Dolphin and sunset cruises aboard the Emerald Magic and bottom
fishing on the America II. Moody's, 194 U.S. 98 East, 850-837-1293.
</P>
<P>
   Reef Runner Excursions, featuring snorkeling, sunset cruises and
harbor tours, at Harborwalk Marina. 850-654-4655.
</P>
<P>
   Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
