 bc-headgen
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; DRUG COVERAGE IS THE RIGHT PRESCRIPTION FOR MEDICARE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,400 words) Includes a 250-word sidebar providing names and
telephone members for the members of the National Bipartisan
Commission on the Future of Medicare. &QL; 
 &UR; By BETSY McCAUGHEY ROSS &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Betsy McCaughey Ross, former lieutenant governor of New York,
redefined the debate on the Clinton health plan with her 1994
magazine article ``No Exit,'' which received the National Magazine
Award and the H.L. Mencken Award. Now Ross turns her attention to
Medicare reform, arguably the most important issue facing America
today. As the national commission on medicare prepares its
recommendations, Ross weighs in with a hard-hitting explanation of
why the commission can't afford NOT to extend Medicare coverage to
prescription drugs for seniors. (slugged:
BC-MCCAUGHEY-ROSS-ON-MEDICARE-NYTSF, priority code w, category code
e) &QL; 
 &UR; ------------------------------------------------- &QC;
</P>
