that certain adult cells long presumed to have irrevocably chosen
what kind of body part they will eventually develop into, can
change direction, go back to the starting line and grow into
something else. If this finding is confirmed, and occurs in people
as well, the implications are potentially be vast. By Nicholas
Wade. (1000 words)
