presidential scholars will be dissecting the achievements, failures
and credibility of a perplexing paradox known as William Jefferson
Clinton. And they probably will be as divided in their opinion of
the 42nd president as we Americans are today. By ROBERT E.
THOMPSON. (Already filed.)
</P>
