   IMMIG-BACKLOG (New York) _ One year after immigration officials
in Washington declared that the reduction of a national backlog of
almost two million people waiting to become Americans was their top
priority, the agency has just revealed new, concrete steps to meet
that goal. The measures include the addition of 300 employees as
well as of a national hot line. By Mirta Ojito.
