   &UR; FINANCIAL  &LR;  (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TRADE-REPORT (Undated) _ In a sign of spreading economic
weakness abroad and shrinking markets for American exports, the
trade deficit widened in November to $15.49 billion after having
narrowed in October to a revised $13.59 billion. In 1998's first 11
months, the deficit was $153.92 billion, above the full-year record
of $153.3 billion, set in 1997. Exports of goods and services fell
2 percent in November. Imports, in contrast, rose 0.4 percent to a
record in November. By Sylvia Nasar.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
