of Hurricane Andrew, has resumed offering new policies. (Sedore,
Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   JOBS _ AUSTIN, Texas _ H.E.B. took to the streets Thursday to
try and find 1,100 new employees, literally standing on street
corners handing out brochures and talking to potential job
candidates. The move is yet another indication of how tight
Austin's job market is. Thursday, the state released figures
showing Austin's unemploy is at 2.3 percent, the lowest on record
for the area and the third-lowest unemployemnt rate in the state.
(Golz, Austin American-Statesman)
