<P>
   UNDATED _ Just about everyone but Rush Limbaugh would agree that
Al Franken is both politically astute and pretty darned funny.
Because Franken's last bestseller was titled ``Rush Limbaugh Is a
Big Fat Idiot and Other Observations,'' Sir Rush of the Right is,
we must concede, allowed to despise Franken's every literary
innard. But Franken's wicked sense of humor is just as sharp when
the author/comedian skewers himself, as proved by ``Why Not Me,'' a
look at Franken's imaginary life as America's president. By JEFF
GUINN. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
