announced in his State of the Union this week that he wanted the
federal government to press schools to end ``social promotion,'' he
was stepping into a longstanding, mine-laden educational debate:
When students fail, is it better to have them repeat the school
year or promote them to the next grade anyway? By Ethan Bronner.
(1600 words)
