senator bounding down the aisle and reaching for the stem-winder of
his political career to save the presidency of his friend, Bill
Clinton. By Francis X. Clines. (950 words)
</P>
<P>
   Moving by  &UR; 9 p.m. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ President Clinton's private lawyer
charged today that House impeachment prosecutors had ignored
evidence that would exonerate the president in an ``attempt to fit
some of the facts into a sinister pattern'' of obstruction of
