 NEW YORK: the series.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   If Reading Great Books Is Your Obsession, You Are Not Alone
</P>
<P>
   Here is information on the groups discussed in the article on
literary societies, in the order mentioned.
</P>
<P>
   AMERICAN FRIENDS OF JAMES JOYCE. Contact: Gerry O'Beirne, (212)
372-1394. Fax: (212) 372-8394. The e-mail address:
gobeirn(AT)ggk.com. Annual membership, $35. Meetings, second
Thursday of each month, 8:30 a.m., American Express Tax and
Business Services, 1185 Ave. of the Americas, near 47th Street,
fourth-floor boardroom.
</P>
<P>
   JAMES JOYCE SOCIETY. Contact: Sidney Feshbach, (413) 549-6470.
Annual membership, $12.50. Next meeting, Feb. 17, 7:30 p.m., at the
Gotham Book Mart, 41 W. 47th St.
</P>
<P>
   FINNEGANS WAKE SOCIETY OF NEW YORK. Contact: Murray J. Gross,
178 Spring St., SoHo, (212) 226-8903. Fax: (212) 226-0996. E-mail:
grossm(AT)idt.net. Meetings, fourth Wednesday of each month, 6 to 8
p.m., at the Gotham Book Mart, 41 W. 47th St., donation, $2.
</P>
<P>
   PROUST SOCIETY OF AMERICA, care of the Mercantile Library, 17 E.
47th St.(212) 755-6710. Annual membership, $15. Meetings, third
Thursday of each month, 5:30 to 7 p.m., in the library's Reading
Room.
</P>
<P>
   JANE AUSTEN SOCIETY OF NORTH AMERICA. Contact: Catalina Hannan,
