<P>
   RESCUED-FOLO (Los Angeles) _ Virtually unscathed from eight
hours in a collapsed trench, Art Garcia met and thanked his
rescuers. Speaking in Spanish, Garcia said he trusted his life to
the firefighters. ``I was following their directions and everything
to stay calm because I knew if I were to rush, I would kill myself
right there,'' he said. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news file.)
