would be studied in an exploration of San Fernando Valley cityhood
is released, estimating that the study would cost between $3.6
million and $8.1 million _ far more than earlier predicted _ and
would take one or two years. In addition, Los Angeles County
supervisors put forth proposals as to who should pay for such a
study. By Michael Coit. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file.)
