   TURBODYNE-STOP (Los Angeles) _ Trading of shares of Turbodyne
Technologies Inc. is halted after the European Association of
Securities Dealers announces it will soon unleash sanctions against
the company because it allegedly issued a number of press releases
which contained false or misleading information. Trading is halted
on both the EASDAQ and NASDAQ boards. By Ben Sullivan. (Will move
in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-FRAUD (Los Angeles) _ The federal government said
Thursday that it sued Assured International and its principal, Sam
E. Harris, for allegedly defrauding 82 investors nationwide. By
Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   NEWHALL-LAND (Los Angeles) _ A surging real estate market has
propelled Newhall Land &AMP; Farming Co. to its best sales year ever,
the Los Angeles-based firm said on Thursday. Revenue hit $304.7
million with second quarter sale of the Valencia Marketplace
shopping center fetching $111 million. By Gregory J. Wilcox. (Will
move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
