<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ Retired Sen. Dale Bumpers, D-Ark.,
uses his country lawyer style and constitutional scholarship to
captivate a divided Senate with a summation of President Clinton's
defense against removal from office that buoyed Senate Democrats'
hopes for quick acquittal. By STEWART M. POWELL, JUDY HOLLAND and
JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
