   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ Rep. Bill Archer of Texas, a key
House committee chairman, says Republicans are willing to go along
with President Clinton's plan to set aside 62 percent of the budget
surplus for the federal retirement system. At the same time,
several House Democrats object to his proposal to invest some of
the surplus in the stock market. By DAN FREEDMAN and JENNIFER
CORBETT DOOREN. (Already filed.)
