promise to pursue a lawsuit against the tobacco industry, Attorney
General Janet Reno says the Justice Department is assembling a task
force for the job. Separately, several lawmakers vow to fight any
federal effort to grab a share of the $246 billion that tobacco
companies promised last year to pay states for smoking-illness
costs. By MARK HELM. (Already filed.)
</P>
