<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Drives change Chandler image
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Falcons quarterback Chris Chandler's reputation
changed in half an hour Sunday, when he led Atlanta on a
last-minute, eight-play, 71-yard game-tying drive in the Metrodome
and then a 10-play, 70-yard drive that set up the game-winning
field goal in the NFC Championship Game.
</P>
<P>
   For most of his 11-year career, Chandler gained attention for
injuries. Leading a team to the Super Bowl, however, is a good way
to change one's image.
</P>
<P>
   Chandler was named NFL Offensive Player of the Week after
completing 27 of 43 passes against the Vikings for 340 yards and
three touchdowns. But it was the drives that did it, as Atlanta
beat the Vikings 30-27 on Morten Andersen's 38-yard field goal with
3:08 left in overtime. Chandler completed seven of nine passes on
the two drives, for 103 yards and a touchdown _ a 151.4 passer
rating. He also rushed for 15 yards.
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons will ride a hot quarterback into Super Bowl XXXIII.
Chandler also was named NFC Offensive Player of the Month in
December, and over the past six games he has a passer rating of
118.6.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was definitely the best drive I've ever been associated
with, no question,'' he said. ``And the second-best would be the
one we ... kicked the field goal on. But a lot of other people had
a big hand in it.''
</P>
<P>
   Chandler, who finished No. 2 in the NFL in 1997 and No. 4 this
season in passer rating, has quarterbacked the Falcons to wins the
past two weeks over both of his Pro Bowl counterparts _ Steve
Young's 49ers, and Randall Cunningham's Vikings.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was as good as I've been around,'' coach Dan Reeves said.
``It was very similar to the drive when we were in Cleveland.''
</P>
<P>
   Reeves referred to the Broncos' 15-play, 98-yard, game-tying
drive in the AFC Championship Game at Cleveland after the 1986
season. The Broncos were quarterbacked by John Elway, who will be
at the helm Jan. 31 in Miami. His 5-yard touchdown pass to Mark
Jackson with seven seconds left pushed the game against Cleveland
to overtime, where Denver won 23-20 on a field goal.
</P>
<P>
   Denver lost Super Bowl XXI 39-20 to the Giants.
</P>
<P>
   ON A ROLL
</P>
<P>
   Chris Chandler was NFC Offensive Player of the Month in
December, and he has maintained the pace in two playoff games.
</P>
