<HEADLINE>
A RULING FAVORS BOTTLER OF COKE 
 (DW)
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Md., Ga.)   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A federal judge Thursday denied a Maryland soft-drink
distributor's request for sanctions against Coca-Cola Enterprises
Inc., the Coca-Cola Co.'s largest bottler, in connection with
documents the bottler filed in a lawsuit.
</P>
<P>
   The judge ruled that a jury would have to determine whether the
documents were fabricated, as lawyers for the distributor, B.K.
Miller of Clinton, Md., have contended.
</P>
<P>
   A spokeswoman for Coca-Cola Enterprises said that the company
was pleased with the ruling, saying it ``validates the company's
position that it has been truthful and has conducted itself
appropriately throughout this litigation.''
</P>
<P>
   B.K. Miller's president, David Miller, noted that ``it wasn't
decided our way'' but added: ``We're not going away.''
</P>
</TEXT>
