 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MEXICO-CATHOLICS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Jan. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Jan.
20, about Roman Catholicism in Latin America referred incorrectly
to the Rev. Ernesto Cardenal, a former Sandinista Culture Minister
whose public scolding by Pope John Paul II during a 1983 visit to
Nicaragua dramatized the Pope's opposition to liberation theology.
Father Cardenal is not a member of the Jesuit order.
</P>
<P>
   BC-DICTIONARY-HOMOSEXUAL-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Jan. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Jan. 19,
about Merriam-Webster's decision to remove references to
homosexuals in its collegiate thesaurus misspelled the surname of
an Internet consultant who raised alarms that slurs were being used
as alternatives to the word ``homosexual'' in the thesaurus's
on-line version. He is John Aravosis, not Aravois.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-INFLATION-NYT (Moved on Wednesday, Jan. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Jan.
20, about a debate in Israel over its anti-inflation policies
misstated the size of the original 1999 budget proposed by Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. It was $53 billion, not $214 billion.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GREAT-BOOKS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Jan. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Jan.
20, about on-line concordances misstated the Web address of a
searchable collection of T. S. Eliot's poetry. It is
www.missouri.edu/tselist/cgi/tsebase.cgi.
</P>
</TEXT>
