<SLUG> BC-IMPEACH-SCHEDULE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SCHEDULE FOR IMPEACHMENT TRIAL 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: See also IMPEACH, IMPEACH-TRIAL, IMPEACH-SCENE,
IMPEACH-REPUBS, IMPEACH-CLINTON, IMPEACH-HYDE) 
(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Following is the expected schedule for the impeachment trial of
President Clinton:
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   1 p.m. A question-and-answer period of as much as 16 hours
begins. Senators will submit questions in writing. Chief Justice
William Rehnquist, who is presiding, will put them to the
prosecutors and defense lawyers.
</P>
<P>
   LATER
</P>
<P>
   Motions to dismiss the case and to subpoena witnesses will be
debated. There will be a vote on dismissal. If that is defeated,
there will be a vote on witnesses.
</P>
<P>
   After deliberations, the Senate would vote on each article of
impeachment.
</P>
<P>
   TELEVISION COVERAGE
</P>
<P>
   Continuous coverage by PBS, CNN, MSNBC, Fox News Channel, Court
TV, C-Span II and National Public Radio.
</P>
</TEXT>
